news.title: Input cost pressure to push cement prices to all-time high: Crisil
news.para: But the earnings before interest, tax, depreciation, and amortisation (Ebitda) of cement makers will decline by Rs 100-150 per tonne this fiscal because of high input costs. Cement sales volume is expected to rise 11-13% on-year this fiscal, albeit on a low base.

news.title: Gujarat government sanctions eight town planning schemes
news.para: These include five draft TP schemes in Ahmedabad, one draft TP scheme each in Bhavnagar and Rajkot and a preliminary TP scheme in Patan.

news.title: Minda Industries leases 47,867 sq ft office space in Pune
news.para: The duration for the lease is 15 years and it is a warm shell space, where the company will begin operations from January 2022 onwards.
